|blank1_info = , |footnotes = }} 'Fresno' ( ) is a city in Central California,
United States, the county seat of Fresno County. As of 2012, the city's
population was 509,039 making it the fifth largest city in California, the
largest inland city in California and the 34th largest in the nation. Fresno is
in the center of the San Joaquin Valley and is the largest city in the Central
Valley, which contains the San Joaquin Valley. Approximately north of Los
Angeles, and south of the state capital, Sacramento. Metropolitan Fresno has a
population of 1,107,416. The name Fresno is the Spanish language word for the
ash tree, and an ash leaf is featured on the city's flag.
